# React Native Mobile App Rules

## 🎯 Project Type
React Native mobile application with Expo

## 📱 Platform Rules
- Target: iOS and Android
- Minimum iOS version: 13.0
- Minimum Android API: 21
- Use Expo managed workflow

## 🎨 UI Framework Rules
- React Native Paper for UI components
- React Navigation for navigation
- Vector Icons for icons
- React Native Reanimated for animations

## 📝 Code Style
- Functional components with hooks
- TypeScript strict mode
- ESLint + Prettier
- Import order: React, third-party, local
- Component props interface naming: ComponentNameProps
- ALWAYS use English for code, comments, and variable names

## 🗃️ State Management
- Zustand for global state management
- Store naming: use[Feature]Store.ts
- Separate stores for different features
- Async actions with proper error handling

## 🌐 Network & Communication
- Axios for HTTP API calls
- Socket.io-client for WebSocket communication
- Centralized API service layer
- Error handling for network requests

## 🌍 Internationalization (i18n)
- react-i18next for internationalization
- i18next for translation management
- expo-localization for device language detection
- Language files in i18n/locales/
- Use t() function for all user-facing text
- Support English and Vietnamese
- Language context for dynamic language switching

## 🔧 Development Rules
- Expo CLI for development
- Metro bundler
- Hot reload enabled
- Debug with React Native Debugger

## 📦 Dependencies Rules
- Expo SDK version pinning
- Minimal native dependencies
- Use Expo modules when possible
- Regular dependency updates

## 🧪 Testing Rules
- Jest for unit tests
- React Native Testing Library
- Detox for E2E tests
- Mock native modules

## 📱 Platform Specific Rules
- Platform-specific code with Platform.select()
- Safe area handling
- Keyboard avoiding behavior
- Biometric authentication support

## 🌐 Language Rules
- **Code**: Always use English for code, comments, variable names
- **UI Text**: Use i18n translation keys (t('key')) for all user-facing text
- **Documentation**: English for all technical documentation 